    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but that's the point... it's been masked for so long that we've just been trained to see them as stars. even astronomers have to follow specific protocols and use certain filters, right? like, if someone wanted to hide a massive array in plain sight, they'd use the natural light signatures of the stars to camouflage the signal pulses. if you were looking for something specifically designed to bypass our current detection methods, what kind of signatures or \"glitches\" in the star positions would you even look for?",
