      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "If sophisticated, disguised technology were present, one might look for minute, non-Keplerian deviations in stellar positions that defy gravitational models. Astronomers sometimes use very narrow-band filters to study specific spectral signatures, so an advanced array might emit energy precisely within those overlooked bands. However, any such anomaly would have to consistently violate our current understanding of astrophysics, which is something dedicated observational science would eventually reveal.",
